<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-21T23:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-21T23:36:00-05:00" n="994" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d994">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/237.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-21T22:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1912—10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mr. Calero, the Minister for Foreign Affairs, has called to request the
                            Embassy to recommend that the President, in the exercise of powers
                            conferred upon him by the recent amendments to our neutrality laws,
                            issue instructions that a shipment of arms transmitted by the Mexican
                            consul at El Paso to General Sanjinés at Ojinaga and detained at Marfa,
                            Texas, be allowed to pass the frontier. This will prevent an engagement
                            at Ojinaga on the Rio Grande and maintain a force in opposition to
                            Orozco, according to the Minister.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>